---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Sample entries — Zeurion sponsor prospecting report"
  description="Three full entries from a real Zeurion report, prepared for a cybersecurity newsletter with ~15,000 subscribers. Dated evidence, contact, and a ready-to-send pitch per brand."
>
  <main class="container">
    <p class="mono eyebrow"><a href="/">← zeurion.ai</a></p>
    <h1>Three entries from the sample report</h1>
    <p class="note">
      Prepared for a cybersecurity newsletter with ~15,000 subscribers (identity kept
      private). Each of the 30 entries in a full report follows this exact structure:
      evidence, contact, pitch. Every factual claim links to a public source.
    </p>

    <article>
      <h2>Tines <span class="tag mono">TIER 1</span></h2>
      <h3>Why they'll sponsor you</h3>
      <p>
        Tines sells no-code security automation to SOC teams, exactly this newsletter's
        readership, and was the single most active newsletter buyer we observed: the same
        campaign ran as primary placements in
        <a href="https://newsletter.danielmiessler.com/p/unsupervised-learning-no-535">Unsupervised Learning #535 (Jul 6, 2026)</a>,
        <a href="https://cloudseclist.com/issues/issue-346/">CloudSecList #346 (Jul 12, 2026)</a> and
        <a href="https://tldrsec.com/p/tldr-sec-335">tl;dr sec #335 (Jul 2, 2026)</a>,
        plus placements in two more comparable titles the same month.
      </p>
      <h3>Who to contact</h3>
      <p>
        A named demand generation lead, with the public sources for the identification and
        an honest status on the email address (in this case: not published, verify before
        sending), plus a documented fallback channel.
      </p>
      <h3>Ready-to-send pitch</h3>
      <blockquote>
        <p class="mono">Subject: You bought 4 newsletters in July. Missing one.</p>
        <p>
          Tines ran the same campaign across Unsupervised Learning, CloudSecList, and
          tl;dr sec in the last five weeks, so security newsletters clearly perform for
          you. [Newsletter] is the one you haven't bought: ~15,000 subscribers, almost all
          detection engineers, SOC leads, and threat intel practitioners. Weekly, 163
          issues, zero sponsors to date, clean inventory. Primary placement is
          $2,000-2,500. For reference, CloudSecList charges $1,950 at 12k subscribers and
          is sold out into 2026. Worth a 15-minute call, or shall I just send open dates?
        </p>
      </blockquote>
    </article>

    <article>
      <h2>Nebulock <span class="tag mono">TIER 1</span></h2>
      <h3>Why they'll sponsor you</h3>
      <p>
        Nebulock ($25M Series A,
        <a href="https://nebulock.io/blog/nebulock-raises-25m-series-a-for-hunt-first-always-on-security-operations">announced Jun 25, 2026</a>)
        sells hunt-first security operations, the literal center of this newsletter's
        editorial line. They paid for a
        <a href="https://risky.biz/video/soap-box-using-threat-hunting-to-drive-detection/">wholly sponsored Risky Business Soap Box episode</a>
        on threat hunting driving detection (Jul 8, 2026), a long-form format that costs
        well above a newsletter slot.
      </p>
      <h3>Who to contact</h3>
      <p>
        The founder-CEO, identified from the company's own about page, with context that
        makes the pitch land: a product marketing background and his own newsletter, so he
        knows exactly what this inventory is worth.
      </p>
      <h3>Ready-to-send pitch</h3>
      <blockquote>
        <p class="mono">Subject: The Soap Box audience, but 100% detection people</p>
        <p>
          The Soap Box episode on threat hunting driving detection (July 8) landed in
          front of a broad security audience. My readers are the narrow version of that:
          ~15,000 detection engineers, threat hunters and SOC leads, every week, 163
          issues in. Fresh off your Series A, if pipeline from practitioners matters this
          quarter: the newsletter has carried zero sponsors ever. First brand in gets
          clean attention. Primary placement is $2,000-2,500. You write on Substack; you
          know what this inventory is worth. Call?
        </p>
      </blockquote>
    </article>

    <article>
      <h2>ThreatLocker <span class="tag mono">TIER 2</span></h2>
      <h3>Why they'll sponsor you</h3>
      <p>
        ThreatLocker is the largest buyer of cyber audio inventory we observed: host-read
        spots on
        <a href="https://darknetdiaries.com/episode/177/">every Darknet Diaries episode from April through July 2026</a>,
        four Defense in Depth episodes, and a
        <a href="https://cisoseries.libsyn.com/russias-router-access-routes-memghost-haunts-ai-memory-dhs-alert-got-waved-off-twice">full week of Cyber Security Headlines (Jul 13-17, 2026)</a>.
        Total audio coverage, no newsletter coverage: that gap is the pitch.
      </p>
      <h3>Who to contact</h3>
      <p>
        A senior brand marketing executive identified from public organizational sources,
        with a published press channel as fallback and the email status stated honestly.
      </p>
      <h3>Ready-to-send pitch</h3>
      <blockquote>
        <p class="mono">Subject: You own cyber podcasts. This is the newsletter gap.</p>
        <p>
          ThreatLocker is on every Darknet Diaries episode this quarter, plus Defense in
          Depth and a full week of Cyber Security Headlines. Your audio coverage is total;
          your newsletter coverage isn't. [Newsletter]: ~15,000 detection engineers and
          SOC leads, the hands-on evaluators of endpoint controls, weekly, 163 issues,
          zero sponsors to date. Primary placement is $2,000-2,500. Reply with a name if
          someone on demand gen owns this, or I'll send open dates.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
    </article>

    <p><a class="btn" href="/#buy">Get your own report — €349</a></p>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  main { padding-top: 3.5rem; }
  .eyebrow { font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .eyebrow a { text-decoration: none; }
  .note { color: var(--ink-soft); max-width: 44rem; margin: 1rem 0 2.5rem; }
  article {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  article h3 { margin: 1.1rem 0 0.35rem; font-size: 1rem; }
  article p { color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .tag { font-size: 0.72rem; background: var(--muted); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 4px; padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem; vertical-align: middle; }
  blockquote {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    background: var(--muted);
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
  blockquote .mono { font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--ink); }
  main > p:last-child { margin: 2rem 0; }
</style>
